--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5e28c2e20bb6c4240a55d8edffb777ec, type: 3}
  m_Name: SteveyStart
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NewDialogueData
  npcName: Stevey
  dialogueLines:
  - LineID: Start
    Speaker: Stevey
    text: Hey kid! Echo, right? I see you here often with your friend Irene. She's
      a sweetheart, eh?
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: II
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
  - LineID: II
    Speaker: Stevey
    text: Anyways, I appreciate you guys keepin' the place clean and honorin' your
      friend, so I thought I'd give you this.
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: III
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
  - LineID: III
    Speaker: Stevey
    text: That there's a lockpick, a remnant from my trouble makin' days! Seein'
      as you're just about in those days yourself, I want you to have it.
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: IV
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
  - LineID: IV
    Speaker: Stevey
    text: To top it off, I've got just the thing you can practice on. Can you open
      up my trunk here? I forgot the key in my truck.
    lineTone: 0
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: V
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
  - LineID: V
    Speaker: Stevey
    text: Don't wanna go all the way back just for a key, but I can't fish without
      my rod!
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: VI
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
  - LineID: VI
    Speaker: Stevey
    text: Plus, if you're good enough to open my trunk, you'll probably be able to
      get into that locked box in the shed! Heck, even I don't remember what's in
      there!
    lineTone: 1
    NPCGender: male
    NextLineID: VI
    endDialogueAfterLine: 0
    choices: []
